CORE INFRASTRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Electron + React + TypeScript desktop app
- SQLite database (database.ts) with base tables:
  teams, players, games, stats, contracts, settings, champions,
  draft_prospects, depth_chart, career_stats_history, hall_of_fame,
  historical_records, news_events, pick_assets, team_trade_overrides,
  player_milestones
- Auto-migrated columns on launch:
  players: position_label, dev_trait, roster_status, injury_status,
           weeks_out, injury_type, waived_by_team_id, waiver_placed_week,
           speed, strength, awareness, throw_accuracy, throw_power,
           catching, route_running, tackle_rating, coverage, pass_rush,
           kickpower, kickaccuracy, runblocking, passblocking,
           morale (INTEGER DEFAULT 75),
           franchise_tagged (INTEGER DEFAULT 0) [migration v3]
  stats: tackles, assisted_tackles, sacks, tfl, forced_fumbles,
         fumble_recoveries, def_interceptions, pass_deflections, def_tds,
         fg_made, fg_att, xp_made, xp_att
  games: home_q1–q4, away_q1–q4, weather
  contracts: guaranteed_amount, guaranteed_pct
  draft_prospects: scouted
- DB indexes on stats(game_id), stats(player_id), stats(team_id),
  stats(team_id, game_id), games(season), games(season, is_simulated)
- player_milestones table — deduplication store with PRIMARY KEY
  (player_id, milestone_key)
- 32 fictional teams auto-seeded on first launch (AFC/NFC, 4 divisions each)
- Fictional player generator: 53 players per team + 176 free agents on fresh
  start (position-specific attributes, dev trait distribution, OVR curves)
- Multiple save files — save picker at launch, lazy DB init via Proxy,
  full save create / load / delete UI (SavePicker.tsx + saveHandlers.ts)
- Reset save / new dynasty supported

