GAME SIMULATION ENGINE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Stats-first scoring: TDs/FGs generated from team ratings; player stats
  derived to always match the scoreboard
- Morale modifier: effective OVR = rating × (1 + (morale − 75) × 0.001)
- Game script: trailing teams pass more; leading teams run more; desperation
  INTs increase when down 14+
- Overtime: TD wins outright; FG gives opponent a chance; no ties
- Weather: clear / rain / snow / wind with pass, rush, score multipliers
- Home field advantage: +0.5 scoring drives home; away QB accuracy penalty
- Depth chart integration: healthy players by position group; cascades
  to backups; targets distributed proportionally

MILESTONE SYSTEM
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Runs after every week and individual game sim
- 4 DB queries (not per-player); 9 career categories, 26 thresholds,
  5 single-season thresholds; fires exactly once per player per threshold

PLAYER LIFECYCLE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Contracts: salary (AAV), years remaining, guaranteed/dead cap
- Morale: 0–100, updated seasonally, affects sim via OVR multiplier
- Franchise Tag / Transition Tag: premium 1-year lock (see Offseason Tab)
- Injuries: random in-game; auto-callup from PS covers starters
- Waiver Wire: CPU claims by worst-record priority
- Progression / Regression: dev trait ceiling, age-based regression,
  breakout bonuses for standout seasons
- Practice Squad Development: age ≤23 PS players get up to +3 OVR bonus
- Season Awards: 6 awards computed at season advance; MVP + DPOY fire news
- Retirement + HOF: age/OVR thresholds; career milestone induction check

CPU GM INTELLIGENCE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Team classification: Contender / Buyer / Neutral / Seller / Rebuilding
- Cap cleanup (cpuRosterCuts): releases lowest value-per-dollar players;
  protects X-Factor and OVR 88+ cornerstones
- CPU resign attempts: offer premium by team type (78%–110% of market)
- Competitive FA bidding engine: market-rate bids, cap-aware, need-weighted
- CPU-vs-CPU in-season trades: Weeks 2–8, capped at 4/week, value-balanced

